{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874466748,"sessionID":"ses_285a46612ffe1UhCW63g46pHPD","part":{"id":"prt_d7a5ba48f001yHUP4GLeGF90JL","messageID":"msg_d7a5b9ae0001sf1xOyxzWKo2RP","sessionID":"ses_285a46612ffe1UhCW63g46pHPD","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_8204ff5081674f1ab1fa2181","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube RBAC manifests","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project in the current working directory. I need to find:\n\n1. Any YAML manifest files related to RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n2. Any spec or requirements documents that describe AR-031 RBAC configuration requirements\n3. Any test files related to RBAC manifests\n4. The overall project structure, especially the manifests/ directory\n\nSearch thoroughly using glob patterns like:\n- **/*.yaml\n- **/*.yml\n- **/manifests/**\n- **/rbac/**\n- **/*rbac*\n- **/*role*\n- **/*serviceaccount*\n- **/*binding*\n\nAlso search for any spec documents, requirements files, or documentation that mentions AR-031 or RBAC requirements.\n\nReturn:\n- Full paths to all relevant YAML manifest files\n- Content summary of each RBAC-related file\n- Any spec/requirements content found\n- Any test files found\n- Overall project structure overview","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285a43f9dffeTSi9mE4IZxro14 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a complete picture of the project. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project: RBAC (AR-031) Exploration Report\n\n### 1. YAML Manifest Files Related to RBAC\n\nThree RBAC-specific Helm template files exist under the `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/` directory:\n\n| # | Full Path | Resources Defined |\n|---|-----------|-------------------|\n| 1 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | ServiceAccount (`workloadmanager`), ClusterRole (`agentcube-workloadmanager`), ClusterRoleBinding (`agentcube-workloadmanager-binding`) |\n| 2 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/router.yaml` | ServiceAccount (`agentcube-router` or custom), Role (`agentcube-router`), RoleBinding (`agentcube-router-binding`) |\n| 3 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml` | ServiceAccount (`volcano-agent-scheduler`), ClusterRole (`agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler`), ClusterRoleBinding (`agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler-binding`) |\n\n**Content Summary of Each RBAC File:**\n\n**workloadmanager.yaml (162 lines):**\n- Gated by `{{- if .Values.workloadmanager.rbac.create }}` (default: `true`)\n- ServiceAccount named `workloadmanager` in release namespace\n- ClusterRole named `agentcube-workloadmanager` with **13 rules** covering: `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims|sandboxtemplates|sandboxwarmpools`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters|agentruntimes`, core `pods`, core `secrets`, `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n- ClusterRoleBinding named `agentcube-workloadmanager-binding` linking the ClusterRole to the ServiceAccount\n\n**router.yaml (53 lines):**\n- Gated by `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}` (default: `false`)\n- ServiceAccount name is configurable via `router.serviceAccountName`, defaults to `agentcube-router`\n- Role (namespace-scoped) named `agentcube-router` with **1 rule**: full CRUD on `secrets`\n- RoleBinding named `agentcube-router-binding`\n\n**volcano-scheduler.yaml (226 lines):**\n- Gated by complex conditional: `{{- if or (and (kindIs \"bool\" $rbacCreate) $rbacCreate) (and (not (kindIs \"bool\" $rbacCreate)) .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled) }}`\n- ServiceAccount named `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- ClusterRole named `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler` with **18 rules** covering: CRDs, events, pods, PVCs, PVs, namespaces, services, nodes, storage classes, PDBs, priority classes, podgroups, configmaps, daemonsets/replicasets/statefulsets, leases, resourceclaims, deviceclasses, nodeshards\n- ClusterRoleBinding named `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler-binding`\n\n**Supporting files:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Defines RBAC control keys: `workloadmanager.rbac.create: true`, `router.rbac.create: false`, `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create: \"\"` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Defines `agentcube.rbacName` and `agentcube.rbacBindingName` template helpers for consistent RBAC resource naming |\n\n---\n\n### 2. AR-031 RBAC Specification / Requirements Documents\n\nFour comprehensive documents exist under `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/`:\n\n| File | Full Path | Description |\n|------|-----------|-------------|\n| **proposal.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md` | High-level proposal: purpose, scope (in/out), architecture before/after, RBAC resource matrix, impact analysis, alternatives considered |\n| **delta-spec.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md` | Detailed Gherkin-style requirements with 11 major requirement sections: directory consolidation, WM RBAC values gate, Volcano RBAC values gate, Router RBAC gate unchanged, ClusterRole naming with `agentcube-` prefix, binding naming with `-binding` suffix, SA naming consistency, permissions unchanged, k8s standard labels, _helpers.tpl name helpers, values.yaml key tree, Helm upgrade backward compatibility, binding integrity, helm lint |\n| **design.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/design.md` | Full design document (689 lines): architecture, package layout (before/after), dependency graph, RBAC resource matrix, naming conventions, values.yaml key tree, label schema, helper implementations, permission rules tables, API contracts (template rendering, conditional logic, binding integrity, label injection, Volcano template split), error handling (migration scenarios, edge cases), testing strategy, implementation steps, follow-up changes |\n| **tasks.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md` | Implementation task breakdown (16 tasks T-001 through T-016) with detailed sub-tasks, acceptance criteria, dependency graph, parallelizable groups, and 22 acceptance criteria (AC1-AC22) |\n\n**Key AR-031 Requirements Summary:**\n- Consolidate all RBAC resources into `templates/rbac/` directory\n- ClusterRole names use `agentcube-<component>` prefix (e.g., `agentcube-workloadmanager`)\n- ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding names use `agentcube-<component>-binding` suffix\n- All RBAC resources get standard Kubernetes labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n- No permission changes (apiGroups/resources/verbs remain identical)\n- Backward compatible via Helm's GVK+name resource tracking\n\n---\n\n### 3. Test Files Related to RBAC Manifests\n\n**Primary RBAC test file:**\n\n| File | Full Path | Description |\n|------|-----------|-------------|\n| **test_render.sh** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test/chart/test_render.sh` | Bash-based Helm chart test suite (271 lines). Contains RBAC-specific tests in sections T-007 and T-008 |\n\n**RBAC-specific test assertions in test_render.sh:**\n\n- **T-007: WM RBAC** (lines 127-144): Validates that `helm template` renders ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding for WorkloadManager; verifies ClusterRole contains `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`, `secrets`, and `tokenreviews`\n- **T-008: Router RBAC conditional** (lines 146-160): Validates Router RBAC is off by default; when enabled via `--set router.rbac.create=true`, it creates Role, RoleBinding, and ServiceAccount; validates custom SA name support\n- **T-011** (lines 55-71): Validates default rendering produces exactly 1 ClusterRole, 1 ServiceAccount, and no Router RBAC (Role) by default\n- **T-009** (lines 162-185): Validates Volcano conditional rendering -- when enabled, creates ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ConfigMap, Service, and Deployment\n\n**Other test files in the project (not RBAC-specific):**\n\n| File | Full Path |\n|------|-----------|\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_code_interpreter.py` |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_data_plane.py` |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_control_plane.py` |\n| `test_agent_runtime.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_agent_runtime.py` |\n| `test_utils.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_utils.py` |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/tests/test_exceptions.py` |\n| Various CLI tests | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/tests/` |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Overall Project Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/                          (project root)\n├── changes/                        # Change requests (AR-001 through AR-031)\n│   └── AR-031/                     # <-- RBAC configuration change\n│       ├── proposal.md\n│       ├── design.md\n│       ├── delta-spec.md\n│       └── tasks.md\n├── manifests/                      # Kubernetes/Helm manifests\n│   └── charts/\n│       └── base/                   # Main Helm chart\n│           ├── Chart.yaml          # Chart metadata (name: agentcube, version: 0.1.0)\n│           ├── values.yaml         # Configuration values (includes RBAC keys)\n│           ├── crds/               # Custom Resource Definitions\n│           │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│           │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n│           └── templates/\n│               ├── _helpers.tpl    # Template helpers (includes rbacName, rbacBindingName)\n│               ├── workloadmanager.yaml       # WM Deployment + Service\n│               ├── agentcube-router.yaml      # Router Deployment + Service\n│               ├── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Volcano ConfigMap + Service + Deployment (RBAC stripped)\n│               └── rbac/                       # <-- RBAC templates directory\n│                   ├── workloadmanager.yaml    # WM SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n│                   ├── router.yaml             # Router SA + Role + RoleBinding\n│                   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml  # Volcano SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n├── test/\n│   └── chart/\n│       └── test_render.sh          # Helm chart rendering tests (includes RBAC tests)\n├── testing/\n│   └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md   # TDD test contract document\n├── test_spec.md                    # Test case specification\n├── delta-spec.md                   # AR-029 delta spec (SDK HTTP client)\n├── design.md                       # AR-029 design document\n├── proposal.md                     # AR-028 proposal (AgentRuntimeClient)\n├── tasks.md\n├── project.md\n├── cmd/                            # CLI tool (Go)\n├── pkg/                            # Go packages\n├── agentd/                         # Agent daemon\n├── cli-toolkit/\n├── client-go/\n├── code-execution/\n├── deployment/\n├── idle-cleanup/\n├── integrations/\n├── python-sdk/                     # Python SDK\n│   └── tests/                      # Python SDK tests\n├── sandbox-orchestration/\n├── session-routing/\n├── session-store/\n├── ci-cd/\n├── go.mod / go.sum\n└── coverage.out\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- The project has 31 change requests (AR-001 through AR-031), with AR-031 being the RBAC configuration change\n- The old `rbac-router.yaml` file at the templates root has already been deleted and replaced by `rbac/router.yaml`\n- The `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` has already been stripped of RBAC resources (now contains only ConfigMap, Service, Deployment)\n- All three RBAC templates are fully implemented with proper conditional gates, naming conventions, and labels\n- The `_helpers.tpl` defines both `agentcube.rbacName` and `agentcube.rbacBindingName` helpers\n- The `values.yaml` correctly defines all three RBAC control keys with proper defaults\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285a43f9dffeTSi9mE4IZxro14","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube RBAC manifests","time":{"start":1775874326624,"end":1775874466744}}}}
